    "chemicalDescription": [
      "Bis-HPMA Poly(Butylene/Hexamethylene Carbonate)/IPDI Copolymer is a urethane polymer formed by a multi-step process. First, a prepolymer is made by reacting 1,4-Butanediol, Hexanediol and Dimethyl Carbonate, which is subsequently reacted with Isophorone Diisocyanate (IPDI). The resulting polymer is end-capped with Hydroxypropyl Methacrylate (HPMA)."
    ],
